To display hello world:

dependencies:

thyme leaf
spring web

PROJECT STRUCTURE:

source/main/java -->controller,model

source/main/resourses
static-->css
application.properties-->file connectivity

pom.xml --> dependencies

Spring, Spring boot difference:

xml-->lots of configuration

convention over configuration-->using annoation-->spring boot understand

Controller-->core-->central part of application

ANNOTATION:
@Controller
@GetMapping("/index") -->url
@ResponseBody  -->response as string

To view a html template:

if no response body , it returns the html iniside
source/main/resourse-->then template/welcome.html-->templates
In this html only we use thyme leaf and get values dynamically


